We need to support content group association with catalog. Support Upsert association end point for catalogs, that will update the association with the current catalog. Create or Update Content group association POST UPSERT → MERGE/REPLACE (need of header param association-update-strategy, default is merge), It will associate the content group with the catalog. The preference of the look-up is based on ID, externalId and docNo. If the record is not found by the look up, than the API will give a validation error the content group is not found. If the records is not found by any id, externalId or docNo, we will give validation error that the given catalog not found. {
    "catalogRef": {
        "id": "", //(Catalog Ref Id)
        "docNo": "", //(Catalog Ref externalId)
        "exnteralId": "" //(Catalog Ref docNo)
    },
  "contentViewRefs" : [
    {
      "id" : "",
      "externalId" : "",
      "docNo" : ""
    },
    {
      "id" : "",
      "externalId" : "",
      "docNo" : ""
    }
  ]
} NOTE: Content view do not have externalId, so we will not do lookup by externalId. Once we implement the externalId in content views, we can reference by externalId. We will give validation error if lookup by externalId is performed. 501 Not Implemented should be thrown.

